cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the design and development of a conversational survey tool, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The evaluation of user acceptance and approach effectiveness also involves aspects of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the focus on questionnaire design and administration could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) category.
